In **FIGURE 4**, it can be observed that carcinoma is one of the study areas since 1990. However, those studies were heavily dependent on the statistical analysis. Many of the 101 articles reported have been written in the last decade because of rapid evolution in ML and DL techniques and their applications in carcinoma diagnosis. Based on the trend, we anticipate that a greater number of studies could emerge within the research domains of automation systems for carcinoma detection and classification.

